WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.480 align:middle line:90%


00:00:02.480 --> 00:00:05.268 align:middle line:90%
>> Prayer for the Earth.

00:00:05.268 --> 00:00:12.720 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:12.720 --> 00:00:17.210 align:middle line:84%
Let us just see
it simply, enough

00:00:17.210 --> 00:00:20.630 align:middle line:84%
to drink in the
spring's radiance.

00:00:20.630 --> 00:00:25.620 align:middle line:84%
The yellow Scotch broom
against green fields

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:29.250 align:middle line:84%
allow our eyes to
reach into the morning.

00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:33.330 align:middle line:84%
Like fingers into
wet grass, our tears

00:00:33.330 --> 00:00:37.480 align:middle line:90%
falling into April's rain.

00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:42.400 align:middle line:84%
We've been too long away
and the need is huge,

00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:46.840 align:middle line:84%
our desire unsteady
in this time.

00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:53.080 align:middle line:84%
Let the invisible wanting burst
to the surface of our skin

00:00:53.080 --> 00:00:58.180 align:middle line:84%
where we may know this world
who holds us so dearly,

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:01.560 align:middle line:84%
even in the middle
of our blindness

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:05.670 align:middle line:84%
and in the beginnings
of our awakening.

00:01:05.670 --> 00:01:09.600 align:middle line:84%
Let us lying face
down in her beauty,

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:13.050 align:middle line:90%
feeding her with our gratitude.

00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:16.510 align:middle line:90%
She is waiting.

00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:18.990 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:36.350 align:middle line:90%


00:01:36.350 --> 00:01:38.830 align:middle line:90%
[WATER RUNNING]

00:01:38.830 --> 00:01:45.278 align:middle line:90%


00:01:45.278 --> 00:01:47.262 align:middle line:90%
[CHIMES TINKLING]

00:01:47.262 --> 00:02:04.170 align:middle line:90%


00:02:04.170 --> 00:02:10.199 align:middle line:84%
This is the cockpit
where I work.

00:02:10.199 --> 00:02:14.310 align:middle line:84%
That's my grandpa
and that's my mom.

00:02:14.310 --> 00:02:19.810 align:middle line:84%
My grandpa was, during
his years in Los Angeles,

00:02:19.810 --> 00:02:22.410 align:middle line:90%
who worked the orange orchards.

00:02:22.410 --> 00:02:30.330 align:middle line:84%
And he was a great mechanic
so he built a speedboat,

00:02:30.330 --> 00:02:33.430 align:middle line:84%
and he built skis that some
say were the first water

00:02:33.430 --> 00:02:35.880 align:middle line:84%
skies in Southern
California that he

00:02:35.880 --> 00:02:38.940 align:middle line:90%
saw in Italian magazine.

00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:42.570 align:middle line:84%
And so my mom was one
of the first people

00:02:42.570 --> 00:02:48.190 align:middle line:84%
to water ski from Mainland
to Catalina Island, 26-miles

00:02:48.190 --> 00:02:51.450 align:middle line:90%
of open ocean, when she was 17.

00:02:51.450 --> 00:02:53.780 align:middle line:90%
She was a tough cookie.

00:02:53.780 --> 00:02:57.070 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:02:57.070 --> 00:03:02.410 align:middle line:84%
My mother, she gave
me to my grandfather

00:03:02.410 --> 00:03:06.080 align:middle line:84%
who was pulling back
from the non-edict world,

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:07.930 align:middle line:90%
from the white world.

00:03:07.930 --> 00:03:14.020 align:middle line:84%
He was born in 1894, and he
came out here to Los Angeles

00:03:14.020 --> 00:03:17.140 align:middle line:90%
when he was 16, 1910.

00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:19.780 align:middle line:84%
Attempted to assimilate,
did fairly well,

00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:24.100 align:middle line:84%
but saw the values were not
his values, so he pulled out,

00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:27.590 align:middle line:84%
bought a little piece of
land on the Stanislaus

00:03:27.590 --> 00:03:31.990 align:middle line:90%
River, Sierra Nevada.

00:03:31.990 --> 00:03:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And my mom gave me to
him when I was five.

00:03:37.390 --> 00:03:42.400 align:middle line:84%
She said I gave you to dad
and I said, your way of life

00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:44.200 align:middle line:90%
is in danger.

00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:46.980 align:middle line:84%
You raise this kid so
it doesn't go away.

00:03:46.980 --> 00:03:50.630 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.630 --> 00:03:52.540 align:middle line:84%
So he taught me how
to be with the land,

00:03:52.540 --> 00:03:54.790 align:middle line:84%
he taught me how
to feel the Earth,

00:03:54.790 --> 00:04:01.560 align:middle line:84%
how to be with animals
wild and domestic, both.

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:04.770 align:middle line:84%
So, yeah I got a very
traditional upbringing

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:07.260 align:middle line:90%
from him.

00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:10.200 align:middle line:84%
As I came up into High
School, I didn't really

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:13.380 align:middle line:84%
know what to do with my
grandfather, teacher.

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.350 align:middle line:84%
Because the whole
world around me

00:04:16.350 --> 00:04:18.370 align:middle line:90%
had a different value system.

00:04:18.370 --> 00:04:21.129 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't believe in
that place, it wasn't mine.

00:04:21.129 --> 00:04:24.881 align:middle line:90%


00:04:24.881 --> 00:04:29.140 align:middle line:84%
In my lifetime, certainly in
my grandfather's lifetime,

00:04:29.140 --> 00:04:34.920 align:middle line:84%
we grew up on a river
that we watched die.

00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:40.360 align:middle line:84%
We watched the spread, we
watch the Box Stores come.

00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:42.990 align:middle line:84%
We watched herds
of deer diminish,

00:04:42.990 --> 00:04:44.550 align:middle line:90%
become smaller and smaller.

00:04:44.550 --> 00:04:48.030 align:middle line:84%
Flocks of birds were, you know,
you might be out in the field

00:04:48.030 --> 00:04:52.050 align:middle line:84%
and see 7 or 800
blackbirds take off at once

00:04:52.050 --> 00:04:54.080 align:middle line:90%
and go across the sun.

00:04:54.080 --> 00:04:58.530 align:middle line:84%
And we watched that
become 6, 5, 4, 3, 200,

00:04:58.530 --> 00:05:02.940 align:middle line:84%
now you're lucky
if you see it 20.

00:05:02.940 --> 00:05:06.200 align:middle line:84%
So all that stuff
on climate change

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:10.470 align:middle line:84%
just blows my mind that
people are in shock about this

00:05:10.470 --> 00:05:13.080 align:middle line:84%
because my elders
have been telling me

00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:14.580 align:middle line:90%
about this my entire life.

00:05:14.580 --> 00:05:17.490 align:middle line:90%


00:05:17.490 --> 00:05:20.610 align:middle line:84%
So now, all of a sudden,
people are waking up

00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:24.420 align:middle line:84%
because their science
tells them what's

00:05:24.420 --> 00:05:26.970 align:middle line:90%
right in front of their face.

00:05:26.970 --> 00:05:31.100 align:middle line:90%
It just boggles the mind.

00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.580 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:33.580 --> 00:06:02.870 align:middle line:90%


00:06:02.870 --> 00:06:06.440 align:middle line:84%
All right, so now
we're in dire straits

00:06:06.440 --> 00:06:14.540 align:middle line:84%
and the question is what about
TEK, Traditional Ecological

00:06:14.540 --> 00:06:19.210 align:middle line:90%
Knowledge, or indigenous wisdom?

00:06:19.210 --> 00:06:25.870 align:middle line:84%
The picture of indigenous wisdom
that people are projecting

00:06:25.870 --> 00:06:31.090 align:middle line:84%
is their own picture of
what was happening here,

00:06:31.090 --> 00:06:33.730 align:middle line:84%
in terms of
sustainability, before they

00:06:33.730 --> 00:06:36.100 align:middle line:84%
came along and
screwed everything up

00:06:36.100 --> 00:06:38.440 align:middle line:90%
with their predatory nature.

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:44.640 align:middle line:84%
And their right to maintain
that predatory nature.

00:06:44.640 --> 00:06:47.340 align:middle line:84%
That it was God-given
manifest destiny

00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:52.535 align:middle line:84%
in whatever shape or form that
predatory nature has taken.

00:06:52.535 --> 00:06:55.520 align:middle line:90%


00:06:55.520 --> 00:07:01.130 align:middle line:84%
The proof of its un-workability
we're completely surrounded by.

00:07:01.130 --> 00:07:04.360 align:middle line:90%


00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:08.500 align:middle line:84%
Now people are listening
because their own picture

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:12.820 align:middle line:84%
of their own future
is threatened.

00:07:12.820 --> 00:07:17.290 align:middle line:84%
So it's a bit ironic to reach
out to Native people now

00:07:17.290 --> 00:07:18.960 align:middle line:90%
to save their butts.

00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:22.040 align:middle line:90%


00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:26.270 align:middle line:84%
The indigenous wisdom
that's really needed

00:07:26.270 --> 00:07:33.270 align:middle line:84%
is how have we
survived a 95% to 98%

00:07:33.270 --> 00:07:39.350 align:middle line:84%
population reduction in a
really short period of time.

00:07:39.350 --> 00:07:44.490 align:middle line:84%
They eliminated, through
massacre, starvation,

00:07:44.490 --> 00:07:49.430 align:middle line:84%
disease from starvation,
90% of the population

00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:54.440 align:middle line:84%
of California Indians
between 1848 and about 1875.

00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:57.950 align:middle line:84%
So we're talking
about one generation.

00:07:57.950 --> 00:07:59.550 align:middle line:90%
One generation.

00:07:59.550 --> 00:08:02.150 align:middle line:84%
So how if California
Indians managed

00:08:02.150 --> 00:08:04.940 align:middle line:84%
to survive that
degree of destruction?

00:08:04.940 --> 00:08:08.836 align:middle line:90%


00:08:08.836 --> 00:08:19.070 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:19.070 --> 00:08:22.640 align:middle line:84%
To really study the genocide,
to study what happened here

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:26.030 align:middle line:84%
is a process of coming
to a point of humility.

00:08:26.030 --> 00:08:30.880 align:middle line:90%


00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:36.700 align:middle line:84%
As long as they are
not willing to deal

00:08:36.700 --> 00:08:43.510 align:middle line:84%
with the human cause and
the cost in all of life

00:08:43.510 --> 00:08:45.730 align:middle line:84%
that they've created
with that attitude,

00:08:45.730 --> 00:08:48.770 align:middle line:84%
taking that same predatory
attitude and saying,

00:08:48.770 --> 00:08:52.390 align:middle line:84%
well, now I want Indigenous
wisdom is really offensive.

00:08:52.390 --> 00:08:54.490 align:middle line:90%
And it's not going to work.

00:08:54.490 --> 00:08:55.390 align:middle line:90%
It will not work.

00:08:55.390 --> 00:09:05.150 align:middle line:90%


00:09:05.150 --> 00:09:09.380 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Kyle Whyte, the Potawatomi
scholar, says, you know,

00:09:09.380 --> 00:09:14.990 align:middle line:84%
unless we come back to right
relationship, to kinship,

00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:16.910 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to
get to the solutions

00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:20.620 align:middle line:90%
that we need long-term.

00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:22.880 align:middle line:84%
There has been so
much destruction

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:25.970 align:middle line:84%
of right relationship
across the board

00:09:25.970 --> 00:09:29.190 align:middle line:90%
that that's going to take time.

00:09:29.190 --> 00:09:31.880 align:middle line:84%
So, within that, there's
going to be a lot of loss.

00:09:31.880 --> 00:09:34.820 align:middle line:90%


00:09:34.820 --> 00:09:39.850 align:middle line:84%
That's where the tears are and
they're the proper reaction.

00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:42.130 align:middle line:90%
They are the proper reaction.

00:09:42.130 --> 00:09:46.000 align:middle line:84%
If we cannot be sorrowful
for what's happening and what

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:51.581 align:middle line:84%
continues to happen, then
we've lost our humanity.

00:09:51.581 --> 00:09:56.770 align:middle line:90%


00:09:56.770 --> 00:10:00.900 align:middle line:84%
This is the real
Indigenous wisdom.

00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:04.110 align:middle line:84%
Everybody needs to
stop and take a look

00:10:04.110 --> 00:10:06.250 align:middle line:90%
and say, how did we get here?

00:10:06.250 --> 00:10:10.980 align:middle line:84%
How does our treatment of
Turtle Island and its people,

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:14.970 align:middle line:84%
and its creatures
show us what we

00:10:14.970 --> 00:10:18.700 align:middle line:90%
need to learn about ourselves.

00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:23.040 align:middle line:84%
This is the Indigenous wisdom
that people need to focus on,

00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:28.440 align:middle line:84%
not their imagined
picture of sustainability.

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:40.700 align:middle line:90%


00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:45.020 align:middle line:84%
No, I'm not a person that
believes the whole propaganda

00:10:45.020 --> 00:10:49.300 align:middle line:84%
that humans are
followed by nature.

00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:51.340 align:middle line:84%
The huge mistakes
that humans are

00:10:51.340 --> 00:10:53.440 align:middle line:84%
making right now, as
far as I'm concerned,

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:57.190 align:middle line:84%
are cultural not
intrinsic to human nature.

00:10:57.190 --> 00:11:06.340 align:middle line:90%


00:11:06.340 --> 00:11:09.610 align:middle line:84%
If we really educate ourselves
and we really learn about this,

00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:15.660 align:middle line:84%
and we really listen and look
and feel what's happening,

00:11:15.660 --> 00:11:21.250 align:middle line:84%
the tears are
enormous sometimes.

00:11:21.250 --> 00:11:24.120 align:middle line:84%
But don't stop there, there's
too much work to be done.

00:11:24.120 --> 00:11:27.430 align:middle line:90%


00:11:27.430 --> 00:11:31.300 align:middle line:84%
And having that communication
with Indigenous people

00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:33.580 align:middle line:90%
is part of that.

00:11:33.580 --> 00:11:36.310 align:middle line:84%
Because nobody is going to
get in their canoe and row

00:11:36.310 --> 00:11:38.920 align:middle line:90%
back over to Europe.

00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:43.900 align:middle line:84%
We've got to figure out how
to do it here, together, now.

00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:46.950 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:46.950 --> 00:12:44.000 align:middle line:90%